The company has scheduled major maintenance outages at its Florence and Fernandina Beach mills in the December quarter. This will impact results in the next quarter. Following the fourth quarter earnings announcement, the Zacks Consensus Estimate for 2014 for Rock-Tenn has gone down 9% to $8.55 per share. (TIS - Snapshot Report), both carrying a Zacks Rank #2 (Buy)., 14854=by Zacks Equity Research   Published on November 22, 2013 |, 20329=On Nov 21, Zacks Investment Research downgraded Rock-Tenn Company to a Zacks Rank #5 (Strong Sell).   Why the Downgrade?   Despite reporting record earnings per share of $2.66 in the fourth quarter on Nov 4, earnings estimates of Rock-Tenn Company underwent sharp downward revisions due to a tempered volume outlook and concerns regarding the negative impact of cost headwinds and maintenance outage on 2014 results. concerns regarding the negative impact of cost headwinds and  on 2014 results. The 91% year-over-year growth in earnings in the fourth quarter was driven by strong operating performance, higher pricing and continued productivity improvements, partially offset by higher commodity costs. To add to its woes, shares of the Norcross, GA-based leading manufacturer of corrugated and consumer packaging and recycling solutions in North America, which had otherwise been enjoying a run above the $100 mark, has dropped to an average of $95 since the earnings release.  OCC (Old Corrugated Containers) prices are reported to be flat to down $5/ton in November.
